# Mars Rover Path Planning Simulator

## Building the Simulator

### Prerequisites
- g++ compiler
- GDAL library
- TIFF library

### Compilation
```bash
# Using make (recommended)
make clean && make

# Manual compilation
g++ -std=c++17 -o simulator simulator.cpp /file_path/dijkstras.cpp /file_path/buf_dem.cpp -I/usr/local/include -L/usr/local/lib -lgdal -ltiff

example: 
g++ -std=c++17 -o simulator /Users/adamcarlson/nasa-jpl-capstone-2024-2025-5/mempa/algorithm/src/rover_standin/simulator.cpp /Users/adamcarlson/nasa-jpl-capstone-2024-2025-5/mempa/algorithm/src/search_algorithms/dijkstras.cpp /Users/adamcarlson/nasa-jpl-capstone-2024-2025-5/mempa/algorithm/src/dem_handler/buf_dem.cpp -I/usr/local/include -L/usr/local/lib -lgdal -ltiff
```

### Setup
Before running the simulator, create the required output directory:
```bash
mkdir -p outdir
```

### Running the Simulator
Use one of the following commands:

```bash
# Run with default coordinates
./simulator -i <path_to_dem_file>

# Run with specific coordinates
./simulator -i <path_to_dem_file> -x <start_x> -y <start_y> -X <end_x> -Y <end_y>

# Example
./simulator -i /path/to/Mars_HRSC_MOLA_BlendDEM_Global_200mp_v2.tif -x 1254 -y 1265 -X 1340 -Y 1338
```

Valid coordinate ranges:
- X: 0 to 106,694
- Y: 0 to 53,347

### Running Multiple Tests
1. First build the simulator
2. Create required directories:
```bash
mkdir -p test_results
mkdir -p outdir
```

3. Run the test script:
```bash
cd tests
./run_tests.sh /path/to/Mars_HRSC_MOLA_BlendDEM_Global_200mp_v2.tif
```

Output will be saved in:
- Test logs: `test_results/test_*_*_*_*.log`
- Path files: `test_results/path_*_*_*_*.txt`